cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SI

This paper presents a computer vision method based on machine learning to create population maps from satellite imagery, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The method also involves identifying individual buildings, which could be categorized under graphics (cs.GR). The use of machine learning also suggests that the paper could be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper's focus on population distribution and risk analysis could also place it under social and information sciences (cs.SI).
